news.title: U.S. payrolls rose 50,000 in December, less than expected; unemployment rate at 4.4%
news.summary: Nonfarm payrolls are expected to rise by 73,000 in December. The unemployment rate is expected to move lower to 4.5%.

news.title: Trump says he’s canceled second wave of attacks on Venezuela
news.summary: Trump said that at least $100 billion will be invested in Venezuela by U.S. oil giants. Trump: At least $10 billion of that money will be spent on infrastructure.

news.title: Iran's leader accuses protesters of acting for Trump
news.summary: Iran's supreme leader accused protesters of acting on behalf of U.S. President Donald Trump. He said protesters destroyed public properties in their own country.

news.title: Trump to meet with oil executives at White House. What we know about U.S. plans for Venezuela
news.summary: The oil industry has been mostly silent on Venezuela as the security situation and stability of the government in Caracas is far from clear. The oil industry is largely focused on the U.S. market.

news.title: Humanoid robots take over CES in Las Vegas as tech industry touts future of AI
news.summary: Some of the biggest companies in tech took to CES this week to show off developments in what they're calling physical AI. Some of the largest tech companies in the U.S. are showing off what they call "physical AI"

news.title: Social Security crisis could leave U.S. retirees worse off than those in poorer countries like Ecuador and Poland
news.summary: Things are already hard for America’s seniors. In less than a decade, they’ll sink even further, experts say.

news.title: The tech investment bubble is going to end — and what comes next may be surprising, this strategist says
news.summary: History suggests AI investment will falter in 2026, says BCA Counterpoint strategist. But the investment implications are notable, he says.

news.title: Trump deals blow to Fannie, Freddie privatization hopes. But there are other options that could lift the stocks.
news.summary: Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac will buy $200 billion worth of mortgage securities. The move could spell the end to the idea that the giants would go public again in massive initial public offerings.

news.title: Choppy quarter to come but stocks will take off afterwards, says this strategist
news.summary: Darius Dale thinks there are at least two more rate cuts to come from the Fed. He's worried about bonds owing to the government’s unsustainable deficit.
